{
  "stem": "1873.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 84.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we were traveling in the direction of the-- of the city called Stryj.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] About 3 kilometers before Stryj, the German conductor was checking the tickets.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we had with us this girl called Langart.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she had a-- a typical Semitic face.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was a typical, I mean dark color hair, the nose wasn't too short.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And she, to hide her face, she did look out of the window pretending that she is looking at the scenery.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "When the German conductor did come asking for the tickets, she turned and showed her tickets.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And she said [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "If she wouldn't talk in German, maybe it will be OK.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But she was a pretty girl and the German could have start to talk with her.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And later she understood she should rather pretend not to understand German.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And she started to back up that she doesn't understand.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Anyway, it was immediately suspicious to the people traveling with us, mostly Ukrainian peasants.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But the-- the German conductor, he wasn't suspicious.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But soon after, Ukrainian militiamen arrived and checking her out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "At that point, I made a mistake.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "If I would act like all my neighbors, oh, they caught a Jew, they will kill her, this-- it will be OK.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But you see I, up until now, if I'm in an embarrassing situation, I start to sweat, perspire.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "At that point, two of us getting red, perspiring, and I didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I took a newspaper I did want to hide my face.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I hold the paper pretending that I'm reading.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And probably I did look-- I did look like a sore thumb, standing-- sticking out between the all other people acting a completely different way.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
